In article <9401282129.A7897wk@asb.com>,  <robert.rothenburg@asb.com> wrote:
>
>I was paging through some back issues of Dr. Dobb's and noticed an
>article on LuC Public Key Encryption... the article claimed that the
>method was more secure against tampering (at least with digital
>signatures) than RSA...
>
>...I don't recall seeing much discussion about it.  Does anybody have
>any info or references on it?
>

The LUC algorithm is not new (the authors seem oblivious to this fact).
Winfried Muller and Winfried Nobauer used Dickson polynomials to make an
RSA-like scheme as far back as 1981.  See my book (page 318) for references.

Bruce
